description:
An implementation of assertion matchers for testing. Similar to Hamcrest for Java

To use, start with "Asserts.That(<value>, <matcher>)".
'<value>' = The value returned from the test.
'<matcher>' = One of the sets of matchers in the 'Matchers' class.


Example: using static JPopadak.CoreMatchers.Matchers.Matchers;

int result = callToSomeFunction();
Assert.That(result, Is(EqualTo(0)));
